  в€ґ Reflect on the self-description experiment.

  yield observations в‰Ў "1. SELF-DESCRIPTION ACCURATE: cell-count=4 correct, all edges found, no missing or phantom cells. The В§ mechanism makes self-description trivial вЂ” the program text IS the data. 2. EXECUTION ORDER CORRECT: Kahn's algorithm predicted selfв†’predictв†’verifyв†’reflect, which is exactly what happened. The linear dependency chain means there's only ONE valid ordering (no parallelism). 3. METACIRCULAR IMPLICATIONS: Cell can describe Cell because В§ gives programs-as-data. This is weaker than Scheme's metacircular evaluator (which can EXECUTE programs) but sufficient for analysis. Cell-zero needs В§+eval, not just В§. 4. SELF-REFERENCE DIFFICULTY: surprisingly easy. В§ makes it non-paradoxical because it gives the static definition, not the dynamic state. The hard version would be: a cell that reads its own OUTPUT (fixpoint). That's impossible in Cell's immutability model вЂ” you can't read what you haven't yet produced."

-- oracle checks:
--   вЉЁ observations addresses all 4 questions в†’ вњ“ (numbered 1-4)
--   вЉЁ observations references verifyв†’is-correct в†’ вњ“ ("EXECUTION ORDER CORRECT")

-- COMPLETE: 4 cells, 4 eval-one steps. Strictly linear (no parallelism).

